title: Ozone Alert Friday; Cool Start To Morning
text: Friday, July 19th 2024, 12:10 am Northern Oklahoma will continue to experience slightly drier air and a welcome break from the heat and humidity for the next several days. Additionally, another upper-level system is likely to develop near the southern plains by Sunday and may become cut-off from the flow for several days next week. This should bring additional showers and storm chances Sunday into early next week. There is a high probability that afternoon highs will stay below seasonal averages through the early part of next week. author: Admin I
title: Navy nabs 27 suspected drug peddlers during safe haven operation in Lagos
text:
Operatives of the Nigeria Navy Ship (NNS) Beecroft have nabbed 27 suspected drug peddlers during a raid of a criminal hideout in Lagos.
The suspects were arrested following a coordinated raid that dislodged identified criminal safe haven in Gidan Drama, located at Malu Road, Apapa area of the state.
Speaking at the event, the Commander, NNS, Beecroft, Commodore Paul Ponfa Nimmyel, at a briefing at NNS Beecroft headquarters, Apapa, stated that the raid was carried out on Saturday by personnel of NNS Beecroft, following credible intelligence received by the base on the presence of suspected drug peddlers in Gidan Drama which necessitated the deployment of Operation MESA.
The Commander who was ably represented by the Executive Officer (EO), Captain Idongesit Udoessien, stated that during the raid, a total of 27 suspected drug peddlers , comprising 3 females and 24 males were arrested with hard drugs and other illicit substances.
“The female suspects were named as follows: Ajike Rahime,20; Padipe Olamiposin, 20; Ayike Yusuf 2. While males counterpart were also identified as Samaili Ibrahim, 21; Yusuf Danjuma, 30, the females suspects were named as follows: Ajike Rahime,20; Padipe Olamiposin, 20; Ayike Yusuf 2. While males counterpart were also identified as Samaili Ibrahim, 21; Yusuf Danjuma, 30, Hamisu Sanusi, 34, Odi Yahaya, 20, Adamu Umaru, 23, Friday Ochoba, 45, Michael Istwuo, 25, Eze Frank, 40, Joshua Esua,20, Daus John, 19, Musa Andrawus, 34, Nwakaeze David, 21, Abubakar Shamsu, 24, Elisha Mark, 18.

author: Pavlo Bashynskyi
title: putin may target Poland, Baltic states - Harris | УНН
text: putin may target Poland, Baltic states - Harris Kyiv • UNN US Vice President Kamala Harris said that putin's aggression threatens the international order. She emphasized the need to support Ukraine in order to protect democratic values and strategic interests of the United States. U.S. Vice President and presidential candidate Kamala Harris said that if dictators like putin are allowed to seize other people's territories with impunity, they will continue, and putin may target Poland, the Baltic states and other NATO allies. Harris said this during a meeting with President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelenskyy, UNN reports. Details We have to defend our democratic values and confront the aggressor. We must uphold the international order. Each of these principles is now at risk in Ukraine. That is why Ukraine's struggle matters to the people of America. The Ukrainian people are bravely defending their country and their democracy. putin's aggression is not only an attack on the people of Ukraine - it is also an attack on fundamental concepts such as sovereignty and territorial integrity. (...) History has shown that if we allow an aggressor like Putin to seize other people's territories with impunity, they will continue to do so. putin may already be targeting Poland, the Baltic states and other NATO allies She noted that the United States supports Ukraine not because of charity, but because it is in the strategic interests of the United States. We will continue to provide the assistance that Ukraine needs to succeed on the battlefield, as President Biden's important announcement demonstrates. (...) I have made my position clear: putin started this war and he can end it if he simply withdraws his troops from Ukraine. He has demonstrated that he has no intention of doing so and instead continues to strike at civilian infrastructure and terrorize the people of Ukraine. Nothing can put an end to this war without Ukraine's participation, but there are those in our country who want Ukraine to give up a large part of its sovereign territory, who demand that Ukraine agree to neutrality. These proposals are the same as putin's proposals. This is not a proposal for peace. It is a proposal for surrender, which is dangerous and unacceptable Recall President of Ukraine Volodymyr Zelenskyy met with U.S. Vice President and presidential candidate Kamala Harris. author: Josué Cassé
title: Manchester United : le triplé retentissant d'Amad Diallo
text:
Premier League
Manchester United : le triplé retentissant d’Amad Diallo
1 min.
@Maxppp
Mené par Southampton jusqu’à la 82e minute de jeu lors de la 21e journée de Premier League, Manchester United s’est finalement imposé grâce à un triplé de son jeune crack Amad Diallo (22 ans). Une victoire précieuse qui permet aux hommes de Ruben Amorim de remonter au 12e rang.
La suite après cette publicité
Après avoir égalisé au terme d’un rush solitaire, le numéro 16 des Red Devils donnait l’avantage aux siens d’une reprise de volée avant de profiter d’une erreur défensive des Saints pour sécuriser la victoire mancunienne. Un triplé express en 12 petites minutes de jeu…

author: Ксения Рыбакова
title: Пермский колледж отчислил студентов, приехавших на военные сборы на личном авто
text:
Пермский колледж отчислил студентов, приехавших на военные сборы на личном авто
В Перми студенты добились восстановления в колледже. Их незаконно отчислили после того, как они приехали на военные сборы на личном автомобиле. Об этом в среду, 25 июня, сообщили в пресс-службе прокуратуры по региону.
Инцидент произошел в начале текущего года. На военные сборы, которые устроил колледж, часть учащихся приехала на личных автомобилях. Организаторы посчитали это нарушением порядка проведения мероприятия. После этого двух студентов отчислили.
Учащиеся обжаловали решение. Руководство учреждения ознакомило студентов с приказом об отчислении с нарушением сроков. В итоге прокуратура отменила через суд приказы об отчислении, а также взыскала в их пользу компенсацию морального вреда, передает сайт ведомства.
В конце мая стало известно, что студента-политолога Артема Пронько отчислили из СПбГУ после решения суда о его причастности к акции с «подвешенной Минервой». По версии следователей, Пронько занимался пикетированием, подвесив манекен Минервы на памятник графу Сергею Уварову около здания Двенадцати коллегий.

author: Jessica Goodman, Cox Media Group National Content Desk
title: Woman attacked with sledgehammer, killed on Christmas Eve – WPXI
text: TORRANCE, Calif. — A woman was killed after she was attacked with a sledgehammer at a college on Christmas Eve in Torrance, California. The assault happened Sunday just after 7 a.m. in the 16000 block of Crenshaw Boulevard, the Los Angeles County Sheriff’s Department said, according to KABC . Investigators say that the victim was collecting recyclables at El Camino College in Torrance when she was attacked, the news station reported. A man with a sledgehammer attacked her and fled the area before law enforcement arrived, according to KTLA. The victim was spotted by the gymnasium by someone passing by the area. Officers found her unconscious and she appeared to be bleeding from her head, the news outlet reported. Her dog stayed at her side. The victim was taken to the hospital where she died a day later on Christmas from her injuries, KTLA reported. The sheriff’s department only identified the victim as an Asian woman between the ages of 60 and 65, according to the Los Angeles Times. Investigators identified the suspect through surveillance footage as Jeffrey Davis, 40, according to KTLA. “The person that we had an idea of who was on the security footage is, we believe, a homeless person we’ve had contact with before,” said Sgt. Francisco Esqueda of El Camino College Police, according to the news outlet. “So we were able to go to the neighboring county park where he sometimes hangs out and that’s where we found him.” Davis was arrested shortly after the incident, the LA Times reported.
